  "description": "Application to vary condition 2 (approved plans) of planning permission P2014/2483/S73  for ‘Part demolition, refurbishment and erection of a part one and part two storey roof extension and new mezzanine floor level for use as office floor space (Class B1) at 29-39 Mount Pleasant. The change of use and refurbishment of part of the buildings including 5 Rosebery Avenue to provide a retail unit (Class A1) and 7 no. residential dwellings (Class C3) and part demolition and erection of a single storey roof extension off Warner Street for residential floor space (Class C3) as well as photovoltaic panels solar thermal panels plant and associated works’. Proposed amendments include reduced massing of 5th floor gallery; reduced massing of Warner Street extension; 1 no. additional residential unit; redesigned cladding on extensions; removal of green wall; relocated entrances; internal reconfiguration; revised energy strategy; and amendments to details required to be submitted by conditions attached to permission ref: P121605\".  The further amendments proposed are re-arrangement of residential and refuse storage entrances on Rosebery Avenue; minor internal reconfigurations to residential and retail block; introduction of heat pump/cooling system to serve residential units with associated condensing unit at 4th floor; addition of rooflight to residential unit; change of facade treatment on Warner St elevation; increase in size of private residential terrace, removal of access from Mount Pleasant elevation and introduction of two access points on Warner Street elevation.",
